{Pál Benno, not to be confused with Pal Benko, won the 7th WCCT 2001-2004 (the
world chess composition tourney, i.e. the world championship for composing a
thematic problem or study) with with study. The theme of the WCCT was (in the
studies section) to show a main variation where a position is reached and then
repeated with a white piece missing, which gives an advantage to white.
compared to the position with that piece. In this lightweight and almost
natural position, the theme is shown multiple times by utilizing stalemate
avoidance. From this study on, "thematic wrong tries" will be shortened to TWT.
I will assign letters and numbers to positions with and without the piece.
White to mvoe and draw. - (position X1)} 1. Rb8+ $1 ({TWT} 1. Rxc7 $2 Qxe4+ 2.
Bxe4 $11 {stalemate (for the same reason Rh5 can't be saved)}) 1... Kxa7 2.
Rb7+ (2. Rb2 $2 Qxh5 $11) (2. Rh8 $2 Qxe4+ $11) (2. Rxe8 $2 $11 {stalemate})
2... Ka8 {(position X2)} 3. Rxc7 $1 Qxh5 {(position Y1)} 4. Rc8+ $1 {(no TWT
here)} ({White must be careful about the perpetual check!} 4. Rf7 $2 Qd1+ $11)
4... Ka7 5. Ra8+ $1 Kxa8 {(position Y2)} 6. c7+ Ka7 7. c8=Q Qxd5 $1 {(position
Z1)} ({As the queen can intervene, it is no longer a perpetual check:} 7...
Qd1+ 8. Qc1 Qd3+ 9. Ka2 Qe2+ 10. Ka1 Qh2 11. Qc5+ Kb8 12. Qb6+ Kc8 13. Be6#) 8.
Qc7+ $1 ({TWT} 8. exd5 $2 $11 {stalemate}) 8... Ka8 9. Qa7+ $1 (9. exd5 $2 $11
{still is stalemate}) 9... Kxa7 {(position Z2)} 10. exd5 $18 1-0

